column1: #Text=The Golden State Warriors defeated the Los Angeles Clippers , 144 - 98 , at Oracle Arena on Wednesday .

#Text=The Warriors ( 40 - 7 ) came in to the game looking to keep pace with the red - hot Clippers ( 30 - 18 ) , who were coming off of a win against the defending champion Cleveland Cavaliers ( 30 - 18 ) in the first round of the playoffs .

column1: #Text=Kevin Durant was the high - point man for the Warriors ( 40 - 18 ) , posting a team - high 23 points on 9 - of - 11 shooting , including 3 - of - 4 from long range .

column1: #Text=Kevin Durant added 23 points , seven assists , four rebounds , one steal and one block , in 29 minutes .
#Text=Klay Thompson added 16 points on 7 - of - 11 shooting , in 27 minutes .

#Text=Austin Rivers chipped in 10 points on 3 - of - 11 shooting , to go along with six rebounds , six assists and one steal , in 38 minutes , while James Michael Felton chipped in 10 points , seven rebounds and five assists , in 28 minutes off the bench .
#Text=The Warriors shot 62 percent from the field , including 50 percent from long range .
#Text=The Clippers were led by Stephen Curry , who finished with 43 points , six assists and nine rebounds .
#Text=Blake Griffin finished with 20 points , four rebounds and two assists , while Blake Griffin chipped in 20 points , four rebounds and two assists .
#Text=JJ Thompson chipped in 16 points , one rebound and one steal .
